## What We Are

aipedia.wiki is an independent encyclopedia of AI tools — reviewed, scored, and verified by a dedicated editorial team. We cover every significant AI tool across 13 categories: coding assistants, writing tools, image generators, video generators, voice tools, automation platforms, search engines, SEO tools, design and app builders, music generators, notes and PKM tools, presentation tools, and research tools.

We are not a directory. Every tool page is a full editorial review: what it does, who it's for, verified pricing, honest scores, real limitations, and clear alternatives.

---

## Editorial Principles

**1. Evidence over opinion.**
Every factual claim — pricing, feature availability, company funding — includes a source link or verification note. We don't publish claims we can't verify.

**2. Honest scores.**
Our four-dimension scoring system (Utility, Value, Moat, Longevity) applies equally to all tools, regardless of whether they have affiliate programs. A tool with a 20% affiliate commission receives the same honest treatment as one with no program. See our full [scoring methodology](/about/scoring/).

**3. No promotional language.**
We track affiliate relationships internally for transparency but never write promotional language about commission structures or affiliate benefits in tool reviews. If a tool has an affiliate program, that's noted in frontmatter for internal use only.

**4. Regular verification.**
Every tool page displays a `Verified` date — the last time we confirmed the tool's pricing, features, and status. We update pages when tools change pricing, ship major features, or shut down.

**5. Failures documented.**
Dead tools, discontinued products, and rebrands are tracked in our [dead tools](/dead/) section. Knowing what failed and why is as useful as knowing what works.

---

## Who We Are

aipedia.wiki is published by an independent editorial team with backgrounds in software engineering, product management, and technical writing. We use the tools we review — most of our pages are written by people who have paid for subscriptions and worked with the products in real contexts.

We do not accept payment for reviews, sponsored placements, or "featured" listings. Tool rankings are determined solely by our scoring methodology.

---

## Affiliate Disclosure

Some tools on aipedia.wiki have affiliate programs. If you click a link to a tool's official website and make a purchase, we may earn a commission at no additional cost to you. This does not influence our editorial scores or written assessments.

Affiliate relationships are tracked in our internal frontmatter (`affiliate: has_program: true`) but never disclosed in page content unless legally required. We apply the same critical lens to tools with affiliate programs as to those without.

---

## Coverage

We aim for comprehensive coverage of every AI tool category. Current site state:

- 150+ tool pages with full editorial reviews
- 13 categories with overview and comparison tables
- Head-to-head comparison pages for the most-searched tool pairs
- Alternatives guides for the most popular tools
- Dead tools archive tracking discontinued products
- Scoring methodology documented at [/about/scoring/](/about/scoring/)

---

## Contact and Corrections

If a price is wrong, a feature has changed, or a tool has shut down, we want to know. Accuracy is the core value. Reach the editorial team at the links in the site footer.

If you believe a score is unfair or based on incorrect information, explain why — we review correction requests and update pages when the evidence warrants it.

